43:15.584 --> 43:19.167
<i>Ms. Oetting had a bad back,
a slipped disk.</i>

43:19.250 --> 43:23.876
<i>Now to walk that with
a bad back and a slipped disk,
it's almost impossible.</i>

43:23.959 --> 43:27.792
I walked it several times during
good weather and it is tough.

43:29.459 --> 43:31.959
<i>But going in the West entrance,
it's flat,</i>

43:32.042 --> 43:33.834
<i>just walked right in.</i>

43:33.918 --> 43:37.000
<i>I believe someone
gave 'em a ride</i>

43:37.083 --> 43:40.876
<i>to the West entrance
of the canyon.</i>

43:40.959 --> 43:43.125
<i>George Spiros
saw the three women</i>

43:43.209 --> 43:46.542
<i>in front of the--
what they call
the root beer stand,</i>

43:46.626 --> 43:48.417
<i>saw them walk past.</i>

43:48.500 --> 43:50.751
<i>Timewise, there's quite
a distance</i>

43:50.834 --> 43:53.417
<i>from the lodge
to that root beer stand,</i>

43:53.500 --> 43:56.792
<i>and then, to go
all the way back...</i>

43:56.876 --> 44:00.500
<i>and then, down
through the trail...</i>

44:00.584 --> 44:02.125
<i>I, I just don't believe it.</i>

44:02.209 --> 44:05.292
I, I, still to this day,
believe that they
were given a ride

44:05.375 --> 44:08.918
to the West entrance
of St. Louis Canyon.

44:11.709 --> 44:14.000
<i>A little later,
another witness</i>

44:14.083 --> 44:17.250
saw a black car
in the parking lot

44:17.334 --> 44:20.000
<i>at, at St. Louis Canyon,
the West entrance.</i>

44:20.083 --> 44:21.751
Person:
<i>Can you read</i>
<i>that witness statement?</i>

44:21.834 --> 44:24.834
Bill:
<i>Yeah. "One man,</i>
<i>leather fringe jacket,</i>

44:24.918 --> 44:27.500
<i>"the two men standing
behind the trunk,</i>

44:27.584 --> 44:32.209
<i>and he was pouring water
on the other man's hand."</i>

44:32.292 --> 44:35.500
<i>Stanley Tucker has
a black Cadillac.</i>

44:35.584 --> 44:37.334
I'm strongly convinced

44:37.417 --> 44:40.125
that Stanley Tucker
gave 'em a ride

44:40.209 --> 44:43.000
<i>to the West entrance
of the canyon.</i>

44:43.083 --> 44:45.709
<i>That put 'em together.</i>

44:45.792 --> 44:48.751
<i>That's why Chester Weger
and Stanley Tucker</i>

44:48.834 --> 44:52.542
<i>were the two main suspects
in this case.</i>

44:53.500 --> 44:54.834
(Person speaking)

44:54.918 --> 44:56.083
No, no.

44:56.167 --> 44:58.209
<i>But that was
up to Harland Warren.</i>

44:58.292 --> 45:01.209
<i>They didn't have enough,
I guess, to prosecute him on.</i>

45:01.292 --> 45:03.876
Uh... and I, still to this day,

45:03.959 --> 45:06.334
I said, I, I don't see how
he did it by himself,

45:06.417 --> 45:08.042
but he said he did.

45:09.125 --> 45:11.876
<i>Was he by himself?</i>

45:12.000 --> 45:13.959
<i>Stanley Tucker,</i>

45:14.042 --> 45:17.167
<i>whether he went
into the canyon with Chester,</i>

45:17.250 --> 45:19.500
<i>only Chester can answer that.</i>

45:25.250 --> 45:26.709
(Person speaking)

45:27.626 --> 45:29.959
He was a good guy.

45:30.042 --> 45:32.584
Stanley, Stanley wouldn't
bother nobody.

45:36.000 --> 45:39.167
Person:
One of the things, Chester,
that I wanted to ask you about,

45:39.250 --> 45:42.459
you wrote this letter
to your father.

45:42.542 --> 45:44.125
This.

45:45.500 --> 45:47.209
What year is this?
Do you know?

45:47.292 --> 45:49.500
Person:
This is December 13th.
It's 1960.

45:49.584 --> 45:55.751
So this, David, actually,
found in a stack of papers.

45:58.626 --> 46:00.417
David:
<i>This letter...</i>

46:00.500 --> 46:02.083
<i>this letter, you know,</i>

46:02.167 --> 46:06.751
<i>incredibly cryptic
and hard to understand.</i>

46:06.834 --> 46:09.000
<i>Chester wrote this
to his father</i>

46:09.083 --> 46:12.375
<i>while he was awaiting trial
at county jail.</i>

46:14.334 --> 46:17.918
<i>"Dear Dad, I don't know
how to say this,</i>

46:18.000 --> 46:21.584
<i>"but I have to, and I don't
want you saying anything.</i>

46:21.667 --> 46:26.834
<i>"If you do, I'll see myself
that I get the electric chair.</i>

46:28.792 --> 46:32.792
<i>"Any ideas you have
that if I never told the truth,</i>

46:32.876 --> 46:35.584
<i>"you were going
to tell the truth yourself</i>

46:35.667 --> 46:38.167
<i>"who killed these people.</i>

46:38.250 --> 46:39.959
<i>"Only I could tell you,</i>

46:40.042 --> 46:44.375
"and despite of what I never
will tell you the real truth.

46:44.459 --> 46:47.792
"Your life, Mom's life,

46:47.876 --> 46:49.417
<i>"Joann's life,</i>

46:49.500 --> 46:54.334
<i>and the kids'
mean more to me than my own."</i>

46:54.417 --> 46:56.334
<i>I think what he's trying
to say is,</i>

46:56.417 --> 47:00.918
"I'm not the murderer,
but I'm harboring information."

47:01.000 --> 47:04.792
"I've only got
two choices, Dad:
to fight it in court,

47:04.876 --> 47:08.709
"and either burn or see
bloody harm come to you,

47:08.792 --> 47:12.751
"or to stick with the story
and to give life to all.

47:12.834 --> 47:17.459
"But I want you to know
I'm not the one.

47:17.542 --> 47:20.959
"Tell no one this
and I promise you this,

47:21.042 --> 47:22.751
"if you do at any time,

47:22.834 --> 47:24.959
"I'll burn because
I won't see you hurt

47:25.042 --> 47:29.083
for something I can't
and I won't ever tell you."

47:29.167 --> 47:30.959
(Mary speaking)

47:38.417 --> 47:39.876
David:
<i>"I'm young.</i>

47:39.959 --> 47:43.459
<i>"I have read the Bible,
and I believe in the Lord,</i>

47:43.542 --> 47:45.918
<i>"and I'm not afraid.</i>

47:46.000 --> 47:49.042
<i>"So, forgive me.</i>

47:49.125 --> 47:51.167
<i>Your son, Chester."</i>

47:54.709 --> 47:58.250
Andy:
<i>"Your son, Chester O. Weger."</i>

48:09.209 --> 48:12.334
Were you ever protecting
anybody else that, actually,
did the murders?

48:12.417 --> 48:14.417
-No, no.
-Okay.

48:14.500 --> 48:16.667
Protecting somebody else
who may have killed somebody--

48:18.083 --> 48:19.542
and you didn't want
to tattle on them?

48:27.959 --> 48:30.292
Andy:
Can we, maybe, take a break?

48:34.334 --> 48:40.209
David:
<i>That letter made me feel</i>
<i>Chester is hiding something.</i>

48:42.375 --> 48:45.709
If it wasn't him, it was someone
else that he had knowledge

48:45.792 --> 48:49.417
<i>because then he came back
and said, "I am not the one."</i>

48:49.500 --> 48:51.667
"The one."

48:55.500 --> 48:58.626
<i>When I was
making the documentary,</i>

48:58.709 --> 49:01.000
<i>the Spiros name kept coming up.</i>

49:01.083 --> 49:04.959
<i>Bill Jansen took
the heat off Spiros,</i>

49:05.042 --> 49:07.584
and started to shine
the light a little bit more
on Stanley Tucker.

49:07.667 --> 49:10.292
<i>I told the police, I said,
"You arrest Stanley Tucker."</i>

49:10.375 --> 49:12.834
<i>I said, "I'm gonna,
I'm gonna testify for him</i>

49:12.918 --> 49:15.250
<i>because I know
the man's innocent.
He was with me."</i>

49:15.334 --> 49:19.918
David:
<i>It's possible that Chester</i>
<i>sticks up for Stanley,</i>

49:20.000 --> 49:22.209
uses Stanley in his alibi

49:22.292 --> 49:25.500
because Chester and Stanley
were together

49:25.584 --> 49:26.959
on the day of the murder.

49:28.125 --> 49:31.584
I, I can't remember
too much about it.

49:31.667 --> 49:33.751
It's been so long ago.

49:35.626 --> 49:39.959
David:
<i>Time has warped the perception,</i>

49:40.042 --> 49:43.667
and I'm not sure
Chester Weger's capable

49:43.751 --> 49:46.667
of answering
the questions anymore.

49:50.751 --> 49:54.334
<i>Andy, I spent a lot of time
interviewing Chester.</i>

49:54.417 --> 49:56.751
Things like his alibi.

49:56.834 --> 49:59.542
That was a very
inconsistent story.

49:59.626 --> 50:03.876
I can't tell you whether
he's telling the truth
when he says he was beaten,

50:04.000 --> 50:07.209
uh, when he says
his alibi was X, Y, and Z.

50:07.292 --> 50:09.500
Uh, those things
may or may not be true.

50:09.584 --> 50:12.667
But there's all the elements
of a false confession.

50:12.751 --> 50:14.792
The crime scene
is not compatible

50:14.876 --> 50:16.959
-with his story
and the confession.
-Right.

50:17.042 --> 50:19.000
That's why I'm sitting
here today.

50:19.083 --> 50:22.959
I think he is not
a reliable storyteller

50:23.042 --> 50:25.125
40, 50, 60 years later.

50:25.209 --> 50:29.292
The damage to a person
after four decades in prison

50:29.375 --> 50:32.542
can be substantial,
especially if you're innocent.

50:32.626 --> 50:36.375
That's why I've looked at,
kind of, the evidence
as opposed to,

50:36.459 --> 50:40.834
you know, whether
he said something that,
that did or didn't make sense.

50:42.459 --> 50:45.417
David:
<i>The ironic thing</i>
<i>about this case</i>

50:45.500 --> 50:47.250
<i>is we've uncovered</i>

50:47.334 --> 50:50.417
<i>an incredible amount
of information,</i>

50:50.500 --> 50:53.709
but I-I-I'm not sure
I can do any more.

50:53.792 --> 50:57.042
<i>It's, kind of, up to Andy Hale
to take it from here.</i>

50:57.125 --> 51:00.042
Andy:
If your dad was here right now,
if I were to say to him,

51:00.125 --> 51:03.667
"Would you be interested
in DNA testing?"
What do you think he would say?

51:03.751 --> 51:06.959
I'm positive
he would be interested
in DNA testing.

51:07.042 --> 51:10.751
<i>That is the only way
conclusion is going to come,</i>

51:10.834 --> 51:15.584
through a DNA match
of either Chester Weger
or another individual.

51:21.834 --> 51:23.918
Andy:
<i>Let's be real,</i>
<i>today is our biggest day.</i>

51:24.000 --> 51:27.667
-We're not asking the court
to declare Chester innocent.
-Right.

51:27.751 --> 51:29.459
We're simply asking,

51:29.542 --> 51:32.959
let us have access
to the physical evidence,

51:33.042 --> 51:36.334
so Microtrace can do analysis.

51:36.417 --> 51:38.500
Carrie:
You know,
we wanna clear his name

51:38.584 --> 51:41.792
before he does pass.
That is my, my biggest fear,

51:41.876 --> 51:44.000
is not being able to do that
for him before he passes--

51:44.083 --> 51:46.834
-Mary: And I think
he'll keep fighting, he will.
-'cause he wants it so bad.

51:46.918 --> 51:49.626
-He wants it so bad.
-Mary: 'Cause that's what
he said all these years.

51:49.709 --> 51:51.834
"I'll fight it 'til
the day I die."

51:51.918 --> 51:54.584
-And I think that's
what has kept him going.
-It's kept him going.

51:54.667 --> 51:57.167
-It really has.
-Mary: Because that's exactly
what he's done.

51:58.709 --> 52:00.626
God is with us.

52:00.709 --> 52:02.125
All the way through.

52:02.209 --> 52:05.292
Andy:
<i>Absolutely, absolutely.</i>

52:07.542 --> 52:10.000
Steve:
<i>Is that why we're here,</i>
<i>looking for justice?</i>

52:10.083 --> 52:12.542
Is it a search for justice,

52:12.626 --> 52:15.751
or is it a search
for a settlement?

52:18.959 --> 52:22.584
Mary:
<i>Everybody thinks</i>
<i>that we're in it for the money.</i>

52:22.667 --> 52:25.375
We're not in it for the money.
I'm not in it for the money.

52:25.459 --> 52:29.584
I want the world,
because this is worldwide,

52:29.667 --> 52:34.083
and I want those people to know
that my brother did not do this.

52:37.918 --> 52:39.959
(Judge speaking)

53:11.709 --> 53:12.751
Andy:
<i>Hallelujah!</i>

53:12.834 --> 53:14.751
-Yeah.
-Mary: Finally, finally.

53:14.834 --> 53:16.375
Oh my gosh.

53:16.459 --> 53:20.042
<i>The judge started talking
about the history of the case.</i>

53:20.125 --> 53:22.209
It sounded like
we were gonna lose again.

53:22.292 --> 53:24.042
But then, when he said,
"You know what?

53:24.125 --> 53:26.375
This isn't fair.
It's not fair."

53:26.459 --> 53:28.334
Can you hear me, young man?

53:28.417 --> 53:29.375
Chester (on phone):
<i>Yes.</i>

53:29.459 --> 53:32.167
So, we took a huge
step forward today.

53:32.250 --> 53:33.626
We'll be able to test
this evidence,

53:33.709 --> 53:35.292
and prove your innocence.
How about that?

53:35.375 --> 53:38.167
We just had to call,
and tell you the good news.

53:38.250 --> 53:39.334
I love you, brother.

53:39.417 --> 53:41.125
All:
Love you, Chester!

53:41.209 --> 53:42.751
(Mary laughs)

53:52.667 --> 53:55.834
Steve:
<i>I'm here to protect the story.</i>

53:55.918 --> 53:58.334
<i>That's the only reason
I'm sitting here.</i>

53:59.626 --> 54:01.626
<i>I stand for the prosecution.</i>

54:02.792 --> 54:04.167
<i>I stand for the truth.</i>

54:04.250 --> 54:06.459
And I know that sounds
pretty noble,

54:06.542 --> 54:08.959
but that's just
what, what I am right now.

54:09.042 --> 54:12.876
And I'll protect this story
until my last breath.

54:15.542 --> 54:17.834
David:
<i>When it comes to true crime,</i>

54:17.918 --> 54:22.125
<i>everyone wants to be
part of solving something.</i>

54:22.209 --> 54:23.667
<i>Decade after decade,</i>

54:23.751 --> 54:25.959
<i>generation after generation,</i>

54:26.042 --> 54:28.584
<i>it snowballed out of control.</i>

54:30.459 --> 54:32.083
(cat meows)

54:32.167 --> 54:35.292
Mary:
<i>I put all these memories away.</i>

54:35.375 --> 54:38.167
<i>Everything just comes
flooding back.</i>

54:38.250 --> 54:42.626
<i>Early this morning,
I, I dreamt about my mom.</i>

54:42.709 --> 54:45.125
She don't have
to go through it no more.

54:48.375 --> 54:51.792
David:
<i>Let's face it, this is</i>
<i>a collateral damage story.</i>

54:51.876 --> 54:55.500
<i>I feel for the families.</i>

54:55.584 --> 54:59.375
<i>They're gonna have
to hear this story again...</i>

55:01.250 --> 55:06.083
<i>be emotionally brought back
to all of this trauma.</i>

55:07.792 --> 55:11.000
<i>I wish my father was alive
to talk to him about this.</i>

55:11.083 --> 55:15.375
<i>You know,
I know deep down he supported</i>
<i>what we were doing</i> .

55:15.459 --> 55:18.751
<i>We're getting everything
out on the table.</i>

55:18.834 --> 55:20.459
<i>What is fact?</i>

55:20.542 --> 55:22.334
<i>What is fiction?</i>

55:22.417 --> 55:27.042
<i>That somebody really looked
into this case.</i>

